<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-031-265 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 401 118</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 21 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Adobe Type Manager to be included in IBM OS/2 2.0.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>McCormick, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Adobe Systems Inc. (Contracts)International Business Machines Corp. (Contracts).andO;Product:   OS/2 2.0 (Operating system) (Design and construction)Type Manager (Printer software) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Operating systemsPrinter software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Adobe Type Manager To Be Included In IBM OS/2 2.0 10/21/91 MOUNTAIN VIEW,CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1991 OCT 21 (NB) -- Adobe Systems has announced that IBMOS/2 version 2.0 will incorporate Adobe Type Manager (ATM) font scalingsoftware.andM;ATM is used to produce different size type in smooth high-quality type foroutput on either Postscript or non-Postscript compatible laser printers andis already shipped with some desktop publishing programs, as well as thecurrent release of OS/2 version 1.3.andM;IBM is expected to strongly push OS/2, the 32-bit version of the multitaskingoperating system developed jointly with Microsoft as a competitor to thephenomenally successful Microsoft Windows 3.0.andM;OS/2 has been virtually aband ned by Microsoft after that company developedit with IBM.andP;  Bill Gates, the head of Microsoft, is reported to have pushedfor a full 32-bit version of OS/2 from the beginning, but bowed to IBMpressure to make the operating system compatible with the vast installed baseof 16-bit IBM-AT computers based on the Intel 80286 microprocessor.andM;(John McCormick/19911021/Press Contact: Patricia J. Pane, Adobe Systems,415-962-3967)</TEXT></DOC>